section: This Services Agreement (this "Agreement") is entered into on October 1, 2019 and is made effective as of November 1, 2019 (the "Effective Date")
explanation: The contract states it's entered into on October 1, 2019, but the Effective Date is November 1, 2019. This misalignment can lead to confusion about when obligations begin. For example, if services were performed between October 1 and November 1, it is unclear if those services are covered under this agreement.

section: Provider shall allow the Recipient to use [ * * * ] at no cost, until December 31, 2021.
explanation: This clause has been redacted, making it difficult to assess the obligation properly. It is unclear what 'use' entails or what implications arise from this free usage ceasing after December 31, 2021. It introduces ambiguity because it is not defined if there will be a cost associated with the usage of the resource after that date.

section: This Agreement be deemed effective as of the Effective Date, Agreement and shall terminate on December 31, 2020, unless terminated earlier in accordance with Section 3.2.
explanation: This sentence is structurally flawed and doesn't make sense. There is some ambiguity to what date the agreement actually goes into effect and what agreement the text is refering to. It's repetitive and unclear and makes the contract unenforceable.
